Make your claim anytime right here in the app. You can either do a voice recording or write to us. We will respond to you as soon as we can and keep you updated throughout the process.

Here's how it works:
* Go to [Make a claim](https://hedvig.page.link/submit-claim)
* Report a claim by telling us what has happened in a voice recording or text
* We will handle your claim as soon as we can

To report a claim via email, send your statement to hedvig@hedvig.com and include:
* Your personal information
* A statement of the incident
* Description of damaged items and compensation sought
* Supporting documents (e.g., receipts, bank statements, photos).

For security reasons, we cannot assist with reporting a claim or provide case updates over the phone.

Once you have reported a claim, our team will get back to you as soon as possible with the next steps. In some cases we might need more information from you to help you further.\n\nSome smaller claims can be handled within minutes in the app. Larger incidents often needs a little more assistance from our service team. If you have any questions about your specific claim, you are always welcome to write to us here in the app.

Processing times vary depending on what has happened and how extensive the specific damage is. For larger incidents, it usually takes a little longer. We always aim to provide our assistance as quickly as we can. \n\nIf you have any questions about your case, you are always welcome to write to us here in the app.

Monthly payments are made by digital direct debit via our partner Trustly. If you have not already connected your direct debit, you can easily do so [here](https://hedvig.page.link/payments). To link your direct debit, you need a Swedish personal number and a mobile BankId. It can take up to 1-3 banking days to approve your linked bankgiro. You can see it in the app as soon as it is approved.

As the withdrawal is made at the end of each month, this means that money can be withdrawn even if the insurance policy is terminated. You only pay for the days that the policy has been active. \n\nExample: Your policy was terminated on June 15. On June 27, the last payment is deducted for the days in June that the policy was active. You only pay for the period between June 1 and 15.

To connect your payment you need a mobile BankID. Digital direct debit is easily connected via the Hedvig app, not through your bank. \n\nIf you cannot connect your direct debit via the Hedvig app, it may be that your bank has a block on digital direct debit. Contact your bank for more information. Are you still having problems connecting your payments? Send us a message here in the app.

Calling Hedvig Global Assistance is always free of charge. If the help you receive on site is covered by the terms and conditions, you will receive compensation without having to pay a deductible.

The service is free of charge if you have been in an accident, fallen seriously ill, have acute dental problems, or are in an emergency situation. However, your phone provider may charge a fee for the call, which you may be able to get compensated through your home insurance. Read your terms and conditions for more information about your coverage and deductible.\n\nFor more basic medical advice, call 1177 Vårdguiden at +46 771-11 77 00.

Yes, your home insurance travel coverage has a base deductible. The amount of your deductible is stated in your insurance letter.\nThe deductible is the portion of the claim amount that you must pay yourself for each claim. If your claim costs are lower than the deductible, the insurance cannot cover them. If your claim costs exceed the deductible, the insurance can cover the amount above the deductible, and Hedvig has the right to reclaim the deductible from you if necessary.

Hedvig Global Assistance (SOS International) serves as Hedvig\'s emergency center for acute illnesses, accidents, and emergencies that occur while you are abroad. If you reach out to them, you can receive various forms of support, such as recommendations for the nearest doctor\'s office, assistance in rebooking flights if necessary, and even obtain a doctor\'s prescription. If you are traveling and require medical care or assistance, it is essential to contact them as soon as possible.

Contact Hedvig Global Assistance (SOS International) as soon as you can for medical assistance and more information, they can determine what help and compensation you may be entitled to. Remember that you need to see a doctor on site and/or contact Hedvig Global Assistance for the insurance to be valid.
I am too sick to go to a doctor. What do I do?

If it is an unexpected and sudden change in your health condition or an accident for which you need medical attention, it is generally considered acute. To provide a more accurate response, we need to examine your particular claim.
How do I know if it counts as acute or not?

Contact Hedvig Global Assistance (SOS International) as soon as you can for medical assistance and further information. They can determine if you are eligible for compensation for a new journey home and, if so, assist you in booking it. Remember that approval in advance by SOS International or Hedvig is required for you to be eligible for compensation for the new journey.
I cannot fly home as planned, what do I do?

If you do not have our add-on, Travel Insurance Plus, your home insurance will not cover specific activities, excursions, or costs that you were unable to use.

However, if you have Travel Insurance Plus as an add-on to your home insurance, you are entitled to compensation for unused activity trips and event costs that you were unable to attend due to a doctor's orders.

If you have been hospitalized, prescribed indoor bed rest by a doctor at your travel destination, or need to return home early (requires prior approval from SOS International or Hedvig), you are entitled to a fixed compensation of 500 SEK per day for unused travel costs. With Travel Protection Plus, this compensation increases to 1,200 – 2,000 SEK per day.
I will miss a prebooked activity due to my illness. Is that covered?

If you have the Travel Protection Plus add-on as a complement to your home insurance, you can receive compensation for a new trip, up to a maximum of 50 000 kr. This applies if you or your travel companion become acutely ill or suffer an accidental injury and are hospitalized or prescribed bed rest indoors at the destination.\n\nThe condition is that the hospital stay or prescribed bed rest exceeds more than half the number of the total travel days, and you must be able to provide a certificate from a qualified doctor at the destination or through a doctor via Hedvig Global Assistance (SOS International). Read your terms and conditions for more information about your protection.
